{
  "_comment": "Configuration for tools/check_upstream.py. Populate `url`, `last_modified`, and `content_length` for each zip from a real HEAD against ODNI's published download URLs. Run check_upstream.py locally first to see how the script handles each entry, then commit the populated baseline. After that, the weekly CI catches drift automatically.",
  "_setup_steps": [
    "URL patterns:",
    "  Dec2022/<PKG>/<PKG>-Public-Standalone.zip      (most ISIM packages)",
    "  Jan2021/<PKG>/<PKG>-Public-Standalone.zip      (NTK, NTK-ACES \u2014 older snapshots)",
    "  <NATO_codename>/<basename>                      (CDR family + WSS variants + older versioned)",
    "    - Foxtrot:    RR-SM",
    "    - Golf_Hotel: ATOM, CDR-RA, WSS-HLG",
    "    - India:      ARH-V3, BRK-V2-SRCH, ICO-V1-ACES, ICO-V10-NTK, OC-NTK-ACES-V1",
    "    - Juliet:     DELIVER, MANAGE, QM, WSS-SIGENC",
    "  (root)/<basename>                               (AUDIT-V4-2011, RR-ID \u2014 flat at ICEA root)",
    "",
    "These are tracked by the canary so we hear about upstream changes, but their content",
    "isn't shipped under data/.",
    "",
    "Setup:",
    "1. Run: python3 tools/check_upstream.py --populate",
    "   to HEAD-validate every URL and capture Last-Modified.",
    "2. Fix any 404s manually.",
    "3. Commit the populated baseline. Weekly CI takes over from there."
  ],
